                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Collection of prayers</title>
                                <incipit>Spiritus sancti gracia illustret et illuminet cor tuum </incipit>
                                <explicit>et potens ad vitam presentem et eternam introductio Per dominum nostrum Iesum etc</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="4r" to="15v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Calendar</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The calendar is of the "composite" type typical of 15th-century Paris (See <ref target="http://manuscripts.org.uk/chd.dk/cals/pariscal.html">Erik Drigsdahl, 1995</ref>), recording one feast (at least) for each day of the year, many with typical spellings, such as <quote>Typhanie</quote> for Epiphany. Notable feasts are:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="4r" to="4r" scheme="folios"/>: St Genevieve (3 Jan.; in gold);</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="4v" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>: St Beatrice (30 Jan.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5v" to="5v" scheme="folios"/>: St Veronica (26 Feb.; <quote>Venice</quote>);</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="6v" to="6v" scheme="folios"/>: St Thecla (24 Mar.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="7v" to="7v" scheme="folios"/>: St Anastasius (26 Apr.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="8v" to="8v" scheme="folios"/>: St Chéron (27 May);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="9r" to="9r" scheme="folios"/>: St Claude of Besançon (6 June);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="9r" to="9r" scheme="folios"/>: St Basil (14 June; <quote>babille</quote>);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="10r" to="10r" scheme="folios"/>: St Landri (14 June; Landry of Paris?);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="10v" to="10v" scheme="folios"/>: St Felix II (29 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="11r" to="11r" scheme="folios"/>: St Claire of Assisi (12 Aug.) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="12r" to="12r" scheme="folios"/>: St <quote>Demettre</quote> (10 Sept.; possibly for St Nemesion (see <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107394">Perdrizet (1933)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="221" to="221" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>));</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="12r" to="12r" scheme="folios"/>: St Venantius of Tours (13 Sept.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="12v" to="12v" scheme="folios"/>: St Hiece (24 Sept.; unidentified);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="13r" to="13r" scheme="folios"/>: St Denis (9 Oct.; in gold);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="13v" to="13v" scheme="folios"/>: St Gabriel (16 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="13v" to="13v" scheme="folios"/>: St Louthiern (19 Oct.; <quote>Luternast</quote>);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="13v" to="13v" scheme="folios"/>: St Gratien of Amiens (23 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="14v" to="14v" scheme="folios"/>: St Romanus (18 Nov.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="14v" to="14v" scheme="folios"/>: St Edmund of Canterbury (19 Nov.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="14v" to="14v" scheme="folios"/>: St Genevieve (27 Nov.; in gold);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="15v" to="15v" scheme="folios"/>: St Séverin of Paris (19 Dec.).</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="16r" to="22r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Gospel readings</title>
                                <rubric>Secundum iohannem</rubric>
                                <incipit>IN principio erat uerbum</incipit>
                                <explicit>sermonem confirmante sequentibus signis Deo gracias</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="22r" to="25v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Obsecro te</title>
                                <rubric xml:lang="fr">Deuote oraison a notre dame </rubric>
                                <incipit>Obsecro te domina</incipit>
                                <explicit>audias et exaudias me miserum dulcissima uirgo maria mater dei et misericordia amen <!--långt pga många olia varianter--></explicit>
                                <note>The bifolium making up <locus from="25" to="25" scheme="folios"/>/ <locus from="30" to="30" scheme="folios"/> has been incorrectly placed in the sequence; it should come after the bifolium making up <locus from="26" to="26" scheme="folios"/> / <locus from="29" to="29" scheme="folios"/>; consequently, <locus from="26r" to="26v" scheme="folios"/> contain text belonging to <foreign xml:lang="la">Obsecro te</foreign>. An early modern hand has added signes-de-renvoi at the relevant places.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="25v" to="31r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">O intemerata (male form)</title>
                                <rubric xml:lang="fr">Aultre oraison a la uierge marie</rubric>
                                <incipit>O Intemerata et in eternum benedicta</incipit>
                                <explicit>ut michi parcat in alia uita concedens michi misericorditer <gap reason="editorial"/> secula seculorum amen <!--långt pga flera versioner-->
                                </explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>Listed after the prayer are the incipits <quote>Pater noster </quote>and <quote>Aue maria</quote>.</p>
                                    <p>The bifolium making up <locus from="25" to="25" scheme="folios"/>/ <locus from="30" to="30" scheme="folios"/> has been incorrectly placed in the sequence; it should come after the bifolium making up <locus from="26" to="26" scheme="folios"/> / <locus from="29" to="29" scheme="folios"/>; consequently, <locus from="26r" to="26v" scheme="folios"/> contain text belonging to <foreign xml:lang="la">Obsecro te</foreign>.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="31v" to="31v" scheme="folios"/>: full-page miniature: St Catherine with her attributes, a sword and a broken wheel; kneeling in prayer in front of her, one of the former owners of the book, Katherine de Brunfay; below: a banner with her name, <quote>KATHERINE DE BRVNFAY</quote>.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="32r" to="107v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Hours of the Virgin</title>
                                <incipit>Domine labia mea aperies <gap reason="editorial"/> Inuitatorium Aue maria gracia plena</incipit>
                                <explicit>ad dona perueniat sempiterna <gap reason="editorial"/> Benedicamus domino Deo gracias</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <locus from="78v" to="78v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="93v" to="93v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="101v" to="101v" scheme="folios"/>: ruling but no text.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="107v" to="111v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Suffrages</title>
                                <rubric>Memoria de sancto iohanne baptista antiphona</rubric>
                                <incipit>Inter natos mulierum</incipit>
                                <explicit>interuentio sit accepta pro nobis <gap reason="editorial"/> secula seculorum Amen</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="107v" to="107v" scheme="folios"/>: John the Baptist;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="108v" to="108v" scheme="folios"/>: St Stephen;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="109r" to="109r" scheme="folios"/>: St Eustace;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="109v" to="109v" scheme="folios"/>: St Lawrence;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="110v" to="110v" scheme="folios"/>: St Maurus;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="111r" to="111r" scheme="folios"/>: St Germanus.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="112r" to="126v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">The seven penitential psalms</title>
                                <incipit>Domine ne in furore tuo arguas me</incipit>
                                <explicit>ne in eternum irascaris nobis</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="126v" to="131r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Litanies and prayers</title>
                                <incipit>Kyrieleyson Christeleyson</incipit>
                                <explicit>piis supplicacionibus consequantur <gap reason="editorial"/> secula seculorum amen</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <locus from="131v" to="131v" scheme="folios"/>: ruling but no text.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="132r" to="141r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Hours of the Holy Cross</title>
                                <incipit>Domine labia mea aperies <gap reason="editorial"/> Patris sapiencia ueritas diuina</incipit>
                                <explicit>Sis michi solacium in mortis agone amen</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="141v" to="148v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Hours of the Holy Spirit</title>
                                <incipit>Domine labia mea aperies <gap reason="editorial"/> Hymnus Nobis sancti spiritus gracia <!--sit data--></incipit>
                                <explicit>uiuamus iugiter celi regione Amen</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="149r" to="198r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Office for the dead</title>
                                <incipit>Antiphona Placebo Psalmus Dilexi quoniam exaudiet dominus</incipit>
                                <explicit>Requiescant in pace Amen</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="198r" to="204v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <textLang mainLang="fr"/>
                                <title type="desc">The Fifteen Joys of the Virgin</title>
                                <rubric>Les xv ioies notre dame</rubric>
                                <incipit>Doulce dame de misericorde mere de dieu</incipit>
                                <explicit>pour tous pecheurs et pecherrelles quil ait mercy de nous Amen Aue maria gracia</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <locus from="198v" to="198v" scheme="folios"/>: ruling but no text.</note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/101506">Leroquais (1927)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="310" to="311" unit="page"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="204v" to="207r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <textLang mainLang="fr"/>
                                <title type="desc">The Seven Requests to Our Lord</title>
                                <rubric>Les v plaies notre seigeur</rubric>
                                <incipit>Doulx dieu doulx pere sancte trinite</incipit>
                                <explicit>huy seras auec moy en paradis Sire <gap reason="editorial"/> Pater noster</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>The rubric notwithstanding, the text corresponds to the Seven Requests edited by <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/101505">Leroquais (1927)</title>
                                        </bibl>, lacking, however, the request relating to the disciples.</p>
                                    <p>The bifolium making up <locus from="206" to="206" scheme="folios"/> / <locus from="209" to="209" scheme="folios"/> has been incorrectly placed in the sequence; it should come after the bifolium making up <locus from="207" to="207" scheme="folios"/> / <locus from="208" to="208" scheme="folios"/>; consequently, the text comes in the incorrect order and <locus from="206v" to="206v" scheme="folios"/> contains text belonging to the rhymed prayer to the Holy Cross. An early modern hand has added signes-de-renvoi at the relevant places.</p>
                                </note>
                                <bibl>
