                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="206v" to="209r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <textLang mainLang="fr"/>
                                <title type="desc">Rhymed prayer to the Holy Cross</title>
                                <incipit>Saincte uraye croiz aouree</incipit>
                                <explicit>Que uray confes puisse mourir Amen</explicit>
                                <note>The bifolium making up <locus from="206" to="206" scheme="folios"/>/ <locus from="209" to="209" scheme="folios"/> has been incorrectly placed in the sequence; it should come after the bifolium making up <locus from="207" to="207" scheme="folios"/> / <locus from="208" to="208" scheme="folios"/> and thus make up the centre of the quire; consequently, the text is interrupted after <locus from="206v" to="206v" scheme="folios"/> and continues on <locus from="209r" to="209r" scheme="folios"/>.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="208r" to="219v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Suffrages</title>
                                <incipit>Uox de celis ad anthonium</incipit>
                                <explicit>et incolumem me perficias <gap reason="editorial"/> Amen</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="208r" to="208r" scheme="folios"/>: St Anthony;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="208v" to="208v" scheme="folios"/>: St Sebastian (continues on <locus from="210r" to="210r" scheme="folios"/>);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="209r" to="209r" scheme="folios"/>: St Michael;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="210v" to="210v" scheme="folios"/>: St Christopher;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="212r" to="212r" scheme="folios"/>: St Dionysius;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="213r" to="213r" scheme="folios"/>: St Nicholas;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="213v" to="213v" scheme="folios"/>: St Catherine;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="214v" to="214v" scheme="folios"/>: St Barbara;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="215v" to="215v" scheme="folios"/>: St Margaret;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="216v" to="216v" scheme="folios"/>: St Genevieve;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="217r" to="217r" scheme="folios"/>: St Avoye (Aurea);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="217v" to="217v" scheme="folios"/>: St Apollonia.</p>
                                    <p>The bifolium making up <locus from="206" to="206" scheme="folios"/> / <locus from="209" to="209" scheme="folios"/> has been incorrectly placed in the sequence; it should come after the bifolium making up <locus from="207" to="207" scheme="folios"/> / <locus from="208" to="208" scheme="folios"/>; consequently, <locus from="209r" to="209r" scheme="folios"/> contains text from the rhymed prayer to the Holy Cross and the suffrages come in the incorrect order; they should begin with St Michael (<locus from="209r" to="209r" scheme="folios"/>), and continue with St Anthony (<locus from="208r" to="208r" scheme="folios"/>). An early modern hand has added signes-de-renvoi at the relevant places.</p>
                                    <p/>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
